activities:
Corporate Executive Board Company (CEB) has a need to extract, compile, process, transfer and use human resource and survey data of their EU-based employees and employees of CEB member organizations.  CEB uses the personal information of EU-based employees for several internal purposes, including: 
•	To administer hiring, promotion, succession planning, discipline, termination, and other human resources transactions;
•	To administer employee benefits, compensation, reimbursement, and related transactions;
•	To process attendance, payroll, and other administrative information;
•	To contact family members in the event of an emergency; 
•	To process health information for administering plans;
•	To administer IT systems; 
•	To comply with applicable employment statutes;
•	To comply with law enforcement inquiries; and
•	Other human resources-related purposes.

CEB also uses, extracts, compiles, processes and transfers personal information from employees of their clients in order to perform the services for which clients  have hired CEB, including:
•	Conducting surveys and other data gathering activities;
•	Analyzing survey responses;
•	Analyzing input from other data collection activities; and
•	Creating reports and other deliverables for clients.

CEB Iconoculture is a future-focused line of comprehensive consumer insights and strategic advisory services that processes personal information of EU-based employees of clients and EU-based survey participants who sign up to participate in survey panels.
